data.value:
Friendly guy looking to make some buddies of his own. Leo loves other dogs. We haven't seen him with cats or kids but can find out!
Leo tested positive for Heartworm disease and has been treated on 10/8. Heartworm is not contagious to people or other pets, but results from mosquito bites. Heartworm, if left utreated, is life threatening, but after treatment, dogs that were heartworm positive should suffer no significant long-term effects as they are kept on a monthly heartworm prevention.
We are happy to talk more in depth about heartworm disease and treatment during the screening process.
